   are a partition of a subset of X and the 
  
    
      
        
          B
          
            i
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle B_{i}}
   likewise a partition of a subset of Y.Using the notation {y: xRy} = xR, a difunctional relation can also be characterized as a relation R such that wherever x1R and x2R have a non-empty intersection, then these two sets coincide; formally 
  
    
      
        
